
[1]juncture

   JUNC'TURE, n. [L. junctura; jungo, to join.]

   1. A joining; union; amity; as the juncture of hearts. [Little used.]

   2. A union of two bodies; a seam; particularly, a joint or
   articulation.

   3. The line or point at which two bodies are joined.

   4. A point of time; particularly, a point rendered critical or
   important by a concurrence of circumstances.
